Leetcode 2218 - https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-value-of-k-coins-from-piles/description/


This is essentially a knapscak problem because from each pile you can pick from 0 to min(k, piles.size()) coins, the way to optimise this is by using prefix sum and precomputing the gain we will get by selecting x coins from a pile

class Solution {
public:
    int dp[1001][2001];
    int maxValueOfCoins(vector<vector<int>>& piles, int k) {

        int n = piles.size();
        vector<vector<int>> prefix;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){

            int sz = piles[i].size();
            vector<int> temp(sz+1,0);

            for(int j=0;j<sz;j++)
                temp[j+1] = temp[j] + piles[i][j];

            prefix.push_back(temp);
        }

        memset(dp, -1, sizeof(dp));

        return helper(prefix,0,k);
    }

    int helper(vector<vector<int>> &prefix,int idx,int k){

        if(idx==prefix.size() || k==0)
            return 0;

        if(dp[idx][k] != -1) return dp[idx][k];

        int ans = 0;

        int pileSize = prefix[idx].size()-1;

        for(int i=0;i<=min(k,pileSize);i++){

            ans = max(ans,
                prefix[idx][i] +
                helper(prefix,idx+1,k-i));
        }

        return dp[idx][k] = ans;
    }
};

2183. Count Array Pairs Divisible by K (vivek malik)

ART : Similar questions exists which says count pairs whose sum is divisable by k, that is done by taking modulo with K getting re and seeing if K - rem exists in map

Somewhat similar idea is used here for any number ex 48 to be divisable by 18 we see what part of 18 is covered by 48 , here it is 6 , 3 must come from somewhere else.
On more close look 6 is the gcd of 48 and 18, so we need some other number whose gcd is 3 with 18 and these two would form the perfect pair 

class Solution {
public:
    long long countPairs(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        long long cnt = 0;

        unordered_map<int, long long> mp;

        for(int i=0; i<nums.size(); i++) {
            int g1 = gcd(nums[i], k); // int g1 = __gcd(nums[i], k); --> Library function

            for(auto &[g2, freq] : mp) {
                if ((1LL * g2 * g1) % k == 0) {
                    cnt += freq;
                }
            }

            mp[g1]++;
        }

        return cnt;
    }

    int gcd (int a, int b) {
        if (b == 0) return a;

        return gcd(b, a % b);
    }
};

Time - map can contain only divisors of k, if k --> 1e5 that number is around 128 , gcd calculations takes log(min(a,b)) time, n*logk*d(divisor count) = n (approx)

